headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored 17 of his 21 points in the second quarter and the Orlando Magic routed the Charlotte Hornets 112-92 on Tuesday night to clinch at least a play-in berth in the Eastern Conference playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Surging Magic clinch at least a play-in spot with 112-92 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green tied a career high with 42 points, and the Houston Rockets closed the third quarter on a 25-6 run en route to their sixth straight victory, 137-114 over the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green's 42 points lift the Rockets to their 6th straight win, 137-114 over the Wizards

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 28 points and wowed the Barclays Center crowd with a high-flying alley-oop dunk, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Brooklyn Nets 104-91 on Tuesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson has high-flying slam, leads Pelicans past Nets 104-91

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 28 points, Luka Doncic had 18 points, 16 assists and 10 rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks held off the San Antonio Spurs 113-107 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving, Luka Doncic lead Mavericks past Spurs 113-107 to sweep season series

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 35 points and 16 rebounds and Michael Porter Jr. scored 13 of his 26 points in the fourth quarter as the Denver Nuggets fended off the undermanned and undersized Minnesota Timberwolves 115-112 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's 35 points pace Nuggets in 115-112 win over short-handed Timberwolves after tight finish
